        <div class="vc-val" style={`color: ${marginOfSafety > 0 ? '#10b981' : '#ef4444'}`}>
          {marginOfSafety > 0 ? '+' : ''}{marginOfSafety}%
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="vc-verdict">
        <div class="vc-verdict-text" style={`color: ${verdictColor}`}>{verdictText}</div>
        <div class="vc-verdict-sub">Based on our base-case DCF assumptions</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology</h2>
  <p>We use a standard two-stage Discounted Cash Flow (DCF) model to value PNC Financial Services Group. Valuing banks is notoriously difficult because "debt" and "cash" mean something fundamentally different to a bank than to a tech company. For a bank, deposits are liabilities (debt), and loans are assets. </p>
  <p>However, we can still value a bank on the pure cash it generates for shareholders: Free Cash Flow (FCF). We project PNC's FCF over the next 5 years, calculate a terminal value for all cash flows beyond year 5, and discount everything back to today using a rate that reflects the risk of the banking sector and the current macroeconomic environment.</p>

  <!-- ═══ ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>Our Assumptions</h2>
  <p>A DCF model is only as good as its inputs. Here are the exact numbers we used, so you can decide if you agree with them.</p>

  <div class="assumptions-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="ac-title">Starting FCF</div>
      <div class="ac-val">${fcf2025}M</div>
      <div class="ac-desc">Reported Free Cash Flow for FY2025.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="ac-title">Growth Rate (Yrs 1-5)</div>
      <div class="ac-val">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="ac-desc">Estimated FCF growth. Large regional banks grow slowly but steadily.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="ac-title">Terminal Rate</div>
      <div class="ac-val">{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="ac-desc">Long-term growth matching long-term inflation.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="ac-title">Discount Rate</div>
      <div class="ac-val">{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="ac-desc">WACC. 10-Yr Treasury is 4.18%. We require 9% to compensate for equity risk.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ FCF TABLE ═══ -->
  <h2>Projected Free Cash Flow</h2>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
          <th>Projected FCF ($M)</th>
          <th>Discount Factor (9%)</th>
          <th>Present Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {projectedFCF.map(p => (
          <tr class={p.year % 2 === 0 ? 'row-highlight' : ''}>
            <td style="text-align:left">Year {p.year}</td>
            <td>${p.fcf.toLocaleString()}</td>
            <td>{p.pvFactor.toFixed(3)}</td>
            <td>${p.pvFCF.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
        ))}
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td colspan="3" style="text-align:left">Total Present Value (Years 1-5)</td>
          <td>${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ TERMINAL VALUE & FAIR VALUE ═══ -->
  <h2>Terminal & Intrinsic Value</h2>
